===Etymology===
From {{enm}}, from {{ang}} [[tunge]]. Cognates include {{la}} [[lingua]]. [[Category:Indo-European root *dn̥ghū-]]

===Noun===
'''tongue''' (''plural'' '''tongues''')

#The flexible muscular [[organ]] in the [[mouth]] that is used to move food around, for tasting and that is moved into various positions to modify the flow of air from the [[lung]]s in order to produce different sounds in [[speech]].
#A [[language]].
#:''He was speaking in his native '''tongue'''.''

===Synonyms===
*(''language''): [[language]], [[lingo]] (''colloquial'')

